\newlabel{fig:select}{{2}{2}{Gaussian selectivity ratio $|\Delta x^*_0|/|\Delta x^*_1|$ vs.\ $\sigma $ (logistic scale) for $a = 3.7$. The exponential decrease predicted by Theorem~\ref {thm:gauss} is manifest across fourteen orders of magnitude. Dashed vertical line: $\sigma = 0.08$ (used in companion numerical experiments)}{figure.2}{}}
